## Rules
- Work autonomously. If something is ambiguous, pick the safest default and record the decision in `.ralph-tui/progress.md`.
- Keep diffs small and focused. One task = one commit.
- Commit messages must be one of: `chore(ralph): ...`, `feat: ...`, `fix: ...`.
- Never commit generated artifacts/outputs/backtests. If needed, update `.gitignore` and untrack generated files (keep them on disk).
- Before committing: review `git status --porcelain` and stage only relevant files (avoid accidental `git add -A`).
- After finishing: update `.ralph-tui/progress.md` (max ~10 bullets, no long text), then commit.

